	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off, if most of you people think you'll ever see this ring drop, you're wrong.  Second it's best for any class, but should go to a warrior.  Third, if you think that because items also have + mana they should go to casters yer crazy.<br><br>Lets see, how pissed would people be if I looted a cloak of piety off trakanon?  There's kind of an unwritten rule that noone gets tank loot till  all the tanks in your guild have better.  This is obviously tank loot for the time being.  When your tanks get something better, maybe you'd have a chance at this ring.  Don't get me wrong, this is an excellent caster ring that i'm sure any of us would die for, but dude its 10ac 15sta 40 hps... what are your tanks wearing?<br><br>By the time you can get this ring, you have a finely honed lvl 57+ army of at least 30 people with mostly epics and near full kael or skyshrine.  Everyone will probably have at least 100 to each resist and epic, so denying a tank an upgrade to their 6ac 65hp ring is just silly.<br><br>If anyone says this is a monk item I'll smack you. =P  I'd pay to see any guild give this ring to anyone but a warrior, that'd be quality entertainment.  Casters would have more hps than warriors and almost the same ac, and we'd all be casterlicious.<br><br>Yes I know there is a 30ac ring that you can get in temple of veeshan, but the chance of you seeing that drop are about the same as winning the lottery.  That one would definately go to a warrior =P<br>&nbsp;<br>Mandicus Lifescourge - Oracle  / Zakani - Disciple / Sleezard - Meatslab / Summan - Necro -Innoruuk</td></tr>
